From: Marc Zyngier <marc.zyngier@arm.com>
Date: Sun, 3 Dec 2017 17:01:39 +0000
Subject: arm64: insn: Add N immediate encoding
Patch-mainline: v4.17-rc1
Git-commit: a264bf34424c815d4565cf1ba0e3cd56b7d5c816
References: bsc#1242778

We're missing the a way to generate the encoding of the N immediate,
which is only a single bit used in a number of instruction that take
an immediate.

Acked-by: Christoffer Dall <christoffer.dall@linaro.org>
Reviewed-by: Catalin Marinas <catalin.marinas@arm.com>
Signed-off-by: Marc Zyngier <marc.zyngier@arm.com>
Acked-by: Shung-Hsi Yu <shung-hsi.yu@suse.com>
---
 arch/arm64/include/asm/insn.h |    1 +
 arch/arm64/kernel/insn.c      |    4 ++++
 2 files changed, 5 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm64/include/asm/insn.h
+++ b/arch/arm64/include/asm/insn.h
@@ -70,6 +70,7 @@ enum aarch64_insn_imm_type {
 	AARCH64_INSN_IMM_6,
 	AARCH64_INSN_IMM_S,
 	AARCH64_INSN_IMM_R,
+	AARCH64_INSN_IMM_N,
 	AARCH64_INSN_IMM_MAX
 };
 
--- a/arch/arm64/kernel/insn.c
+++ b/arch/arm64/kernel/insn.c
@@ -343,6 +343,10 @@ static int __kprobes aarch64_get_imm_shi
 		mask = BIT(6) - 1;
 		shift = 16;
 		break;
+	case AARCH64_INSN_IMM_N:
+		mask = 1;
+		shift = 22;
+		break;
 	default:
 		return -EINVAL;
 	}
